ated_at":"2024-01-28T09:36:22Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"### Comment:

As I have no access to Mac hardware, I can not check myself. But it seems to me, that the missing `ISO_Fortran_binding.h` issue for the gfortran compilers, which were fixed in conda-forge/ctng-compilers-feedstock#123 for Linux, is still available on OSX_64. At least, the building of MPICH with modern Fortran interfaces, which requires this include file, seems to be successful now on all platforms, except osx_64, where the compiler capability detection fails due to the missing include file (conda-forge/mpich-feedstock#84).

